timelineItems.comment: Victor Obinna (Nigeria) wins a free kick on the right wing.
Foul by Andrés Guardado (Mexico).

timelineItems.name: Tiwa Works
timelineItems.text: The smoke has come out!! lol check out toilet rolls being thrown from the upper level! #mexico #mexican #nigeria #naija #nigeriavsmexico

timelineItems.comment: Foul by John Obi Mikel (Nigeria).
Carlos Peña (Mexico) wins a free kick in the defensive half.

timelineItems.name: Soccerly
timelineItems.text: Fifteen minutes left in #MEXvNIG match. Fans starting to sing in the absence of goals. Will there be a last minute hero?

timelineItems.comment: Andrés Guardado (Mexico) wins a free kick on the left wing.
Foul by Victor Obinna (Nigeria).

timelineItems.name: Goal.com Nigeria
timelineItems.text: It's all Mexico now, and the Super Eagles are lucky to still be level, Ejide pulled off some great saves...

timelineItems.comment: Foul by Emmanuel Emenike (Nigeria).
Rafael Márquez (Mexico) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Corner,  Mexico. Conceded by Godfrey Oboabona.

timelineItems.name: Nedu Echianu
timelineItems.text: Emenike has been complaining too much...he gets a yellow for his efforts. #MEXvNIG

timelineItems.comment: Dangerous play by Paul Aguilar (Mexico).
Imoh Ezekiel (Nigeria) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Attempt missed. Victor Obinna (Nigeria) left footed shot from outside the box is too high. Assisted by Ramón Azeez with a cross.
Attempt saved. Alan Pulido (Mexico) right footed shot from outside the box is saved in the centre of the goal.
Carlos Peña (Mexico) wins a free kick on the left wing.
Foul by Victor Obinna (Nigeria).

timelineItems.name: Prof.Pethiano Peters
timelineItems.text: #SuperEagles number one problem is good finishing. Loads of chances. #MTNfootball

timelineItems.comment: Corner,  Mexico. Conceded by John Obi Mikel.
Attempt missed. Alan Pulido (Mexico) header from the centre of the box is close, but misses to the right. Assisted by Javier Aquino with a cross following a corner.

timelineItems.name: Love you Sweetie®
timelineItems.text: RECORD made in USA Over 68,000 people at the Georgia dome!!! Record turnout for a soccer game!! #NigeriaVsMexico GO #NIGERIA #SUPEREAGLES

timelineItems.comment: Elderson (Nigeria) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Foul by Alan Pulido (Mexico).

timelineItems.name: Sheyi Adeyemi
timelineItems.text: Well, one position is pretty set for the Eagles - that of the Goalie. The two we have are pretty good. #SuperEagles

timelineItems.name: Tunde
timelineItems.text: They have been very dangerous on set pieces though our boys are taller #MEXvNIG

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Victor Obinna (Nigeria) right footed shot from outside the box is close, but misses to the right. Assisted by Emmanuel Emenike.

timelineItems.name: Goal.com Nigeria
timelineItems.text: Nigeria are barely 'surviving' in these final minutes. Mexico edging closer to scoring, Ejide in superb form...what fine keepers we have. CC

timelineItems.comment: Attempt saved. Alan Pulido (Mexico) right footed shot from the centre of the box is saved in the centre of the goal.
Kenneth Omeruo (Nigeria) wins a free kick in the defensive half.
Foul by Oribe Peralta (Mexico).

timelineItems.name: Tom Marshall
timelineItems.text: Mexico set up as expected in defense, with Moreno on left of back 3, Reyes on right, Marquez in center.

timelineItems.comment: Attempt saved. Imoh Ezekiel (Nigeria) left footed shot from the right side of the box is saved in the bottom right corner. Assisted by Victor Obinna.

timelineItems.name: CK
timelineItems.text: Throwing smoke bombs on the field is dumb. #ElTri #Mexico

timelineItems.name: Anthony DeAngelo
timelineItems.text: You keep it classy #eltri fans. Way to disrupt your own counter-attack.

timelineItems.comment: John Obi Mikel (Nigeria) wins a free kick in the attacking half.
Foul by Javier Aquino (Mexico).
Offside, Nigeria. Emmanuel Emenike tries a through ball, but Imoh Ezekiel is caught offside.
Hand ball by John Obi Mikel (Nigeria).

timelineItems.name: Joe Ryan
timelineItems.text: #ElTri is terrible, no scoring punch and poor organization. #noimagination

timelineItems.name: Mr. Igoni Kitoye. M
timelineItems.text: Great tackles & pass from #SuperEagles but we need to put pressure on their defences & try to create d needed chances and score, nah witin..

timelineItems.name: Soccerly
timelineItems.text: #MEXvNIG ends with a 0-0 score at the Georgia Dome. Next up for #ElTri is the match against #USMNT on April 2 in Phoenix!

timelineItems.name: Tom Marshall
timelineItems.text: Mexico 0-0 Nigeria. No doubt Memo Ochoa was Mexico's man of the match.

timelineItems.name: Ebuka Obi-Uchendu
timelineItems.text: Full time. 0-0. Our goalkeepers won tonight. #SuperEagles

timelineItems.comment: Attempt missed. Victor Obinna (Nigeria) right footed shot from outside the box misses to the left from a direct free kick.
Second Half ends, Mexico 0, Nigeria 0.
